texts.text: >The Liberators' hopes of reclaiming the Tokyo Branch's territory look dim
>as the darkness that spawns the unkillable demons continues to spread.
>Baldur and his worshippers move to each area to fell these demons,
>but the battle has spread to include the entirety of Tokyo
>as the darkness works day and night to completely consume the entire city.
>Strange and unpredictable weather phenomena still plague Tokyo.
>The government has ordered an evacuation and the nation's capital
>now lay in darkness and demons have taken over the abandoned parts of the city.
>But some still fight on...
>A temple somewhere in the city...
*Pant*
This is rough. We really need to protect this spot but...
The demons have already taken over the surrounding space.
Are you sure it's gonna be okay?
Yes. I can see it now. Those demons look disorganized.
So we just need to get over there?
Got ya!
*Shriek*
Easier said than done. There's no end to these demons.
We need to hurry or we won't have an escape route...
Shit! Ririn, behind you...!
Crap...!
>Ririn somehow manages to dodge the demon's attack!
Oww...! No, my leg...!
*Scream*
No...
>You put yourself between the demon and Ririn!
>A sharp pain runs through your shoulder...!
There!!
*Gasp*
Sorry, Newbie... I...
Can you stand?
That can wait.
I... I'm fine!
It hurts, but I can keep going!
Right...! Let's just get out of here!
Two out of four wounded. Seiran, we need to fall back.
Ha!
*Scream*
*Shriek*
They revive so fast. And we're pretty much out of gas.
I hope we can still get out in one piece...!
>Countless demons charge towards your position...
Baldur, there!
Very well.
*Roar*
*Scream*
*Roar*
You are safe, Liberators.
Baldur, and the leader of that group... You guys haven't missed a beat, I guess...
All of those in just one go...
Oh, thank god... We didn't lose anyone.
Are you alright, Ririn? Newbie?
I think I'm okay. I hope I don't get a gross scar from this.
I'm okay...
It's just a scratch.
Ugh. Drop the tough guy act!
She's right, and I'm so sorry...
Just a scratch... It's just like you to say something like that.
But we got out of there alright thanks to you.
And Baldur. He really saved our hides.
I don't want to think about what would've happened if you didn't show up...
Oh... Sorry, there's something else I need to do while I can.
There we go.
Ah, a charm. For a barrier?
From where the Dragon Stream flows... Did you secure a spiritual site?
Oh, you're very sharp.
But it can only extend to the edge of this site. Will it be enough?
I really can't say how long it'll hold...
But since Tokyo's been turned into this kind of place,
we need to protect the few places that've been left to us.
The rest of the Liberators have been securing every place they can too.
Demons can appear anywhere in Tokyo now in its current state.
You have no hope of defeating them. Why do you continue to put yourselves in harm's way?
Your powers are indeed uncanny and even special.
But without this app, you return to simply being ordinary humans.
One false move and it'll be the end for all of you.
Even you are powerless in the face of certain enemies or situations.
Why is it that you continue to persist even if you are in mortal danger?
Because...
Come on, spit it out...
I mean, we know this is bad... But...
I want to protect my family, I guess?
I care about my little brother and sister, and mom who works so hard.
It'd be awful to just let the world rot away without doing anything, right?
Our homes are gone, our lives are ruined but...
We know things, so we can't just be bystanders.
We have no choice.
We know things and have the power to maybe do something about it.
And our chances haven't hit 0% yet.
We need to do this.
We want to do this.
Sorry, Mr. Leader. These kids like to leap before looking.
They're doing what they feel they need to because they want to.
And they'll put their lives on the line just for that.
So we can't just leave them to fight this thing alone.
You're no different.
What?
You're also fighting to save this world, right?
In order to do that, you toiled away to somehow summon Baldur, no?
We summon demons without really knowing much about this app,
but it's actually really hard, right?
You're looking for ways to deal with this,
so in the end, we're not really all that different.
Yo, Seiran! How's things on your end?
Oh, Megakin. I was just about to call you.
We managed to put a barrier around this spot.
The darkness dissipated, so we might be able to make this a safe point.
Nice! Good job, y'all!
But we have two wounded. It might take a while to get back.
Wounded? Yo, how they doin'?
They're hanging on. But we need to put a pause on things.
Aight. Be careful when you start headin' back yo.
To be honest, there ain't much in the way of safe places anymore.
I'm well aware of that. We'll be going now...
Baldur, thank you very much.
Shionyan, she says we're going!
Huh?
(How can these demons be "unkillable"? What's the problem?)
(It's not like our attacks don't work on them. They're not repelling or absorbing them either.)
(They only appear in the darkness. So this darkness holds the key to this?)
(What happened when the darkness wasn't as thick?)
(The demons in Seiran's video revived slower than they do now...)
(Slower...)
Shionyan!
We're leaving! Wake up so we can go!
I can't completely say for sure yet. We need proof...
>The Liberators take their leave...
Doing what you can...
Summoners. There is something you must know.
In time, I must return to the underworld.
What...?!
Fear not. Before that time comes, I shall cleanse this darkness.
And after that...?
If we lose you, Baldur, this world will be faced with another disaster.
The end is simply being postponed.
Is this world simply doomed to be destroyed?!
With your power,
this darkness can surely be cleaned in one fell swoop!
Why is it that you shy away from doing so?
Is it that you have decided to condemn this world to face its fate...?
Do you truly believe that?
Believe what...?
Let us go.
Bear witness with your own eyes. The true fate of this world...
